  "texts": [
    "UMLS framework is designed to standardize medical vocabularies and ontologies.",
    "Text parsing tools designed on top of UMLS identify medical concepts from free-text and map them to unique identifiers (CUI).",
    "Concepts are categorized into 127 \"semtypes\".",
    "We selected 36 semtypes relevant to treatment, symptoms, side effects, clinical status and anatomical details.",
    "Filtered text from clinical notes was divided into sentences and passed through UMLS parser one by one and relevant medical entities and their location in the sentences were stored."
  ],
